100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 23, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on disarmament and the promotion of international peace. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition continued to stir public sentiment, with calls for reform gaining traction amid rising crime rates. Meanwhile, tensions escalated in the Middle East as British troops faced unrest in Palestine, highlighting the region's volatile political landscape.
